Description: Fix CVE-2024-21634 - StackOverflowError DoS in Amazon Ion Java
 Adapted backport for software.amazon.ion:ion-java 1.0.2.
 .
 Two changes are applied:
 .
 1. IonReaderTextRawTokensX.skip_over_container is converted from recursive
    descent to an iterative loop backed by an ArrayList terminator stack.
    A deeply nested Ion text document can no longer blow the JVM stack while
    being scanned by the text reader.
 .
 2. Equivalence.ionEqualsImpl / ionCompareToImpl / compareStructs /
    compareSequences / Field gain a depth counter and refuse to recurse past
    a hard limit of 1000 levels (configurable upstream via the post-1.10.5
    Equivalence.Configuration / Builder API which does not yet exist on
    1.0.2). When the limit is exceeded an IonException is thrown rather than
    consuming unbounded JVM stack.
 .
 Source paths in the upstream commits live under src/com/amazon/ion/...
 because upstream renamed the Maven coordinate after 1.0.2; on 1.0.2 the
 target paths are src/software/amazon/ion/... and the patch reflects that.
Origin: backport, https://github.com/amazon-ion/ion-java/commit/3fb88a1043cbeb8c0ac08630a2d5327f7aefff1b
 https://github.com/amazon-ion/ion-java/commit/05dab5bda099f94c01a19422d39e54fba8bb110e
